The Core Concept: Giving Claude Code the Right Tools
Claude Code operates best when you think of it like orchestrating a crew rather than hiring one person to do everything. There are three distinct layers:
1. MCP Servers — External integrations / live data
These give Claude Code access to systems it otherwise can't touch.
Finding good ones:

modelcontextprotocol.io/servers — the official registry
mcp.so — community-curated directory
awesome-mcp-servers on GitHub — heavily starred, well-maintained list
Search GitHub directly: topic:mcp-server

High-value MCPs for your stack specifically:
